# GCP deploy & SSH (Robert Todd Trends)

Read **`deployment/GCP-DEPLOY.md`** and **`AGENTS.md`** before deploying or pulling production state.

## Deploy (always use git, not rsync)

1. `gh auth switch --user thedoctor0124` and `gh auth setup-git` if push fails with 403.
2. `git push origin main` to `thedoctor0124/robert-todd-trends`.
3. On server: `ssh TrendsGCP` → `cd /var/www/looptrends` → `git pull origin main` → `composer install --no-dev --optimize-autoloader` → `npm ci && npm run build` → `php artisan migrate --force` → `php artisan optimize:clear` → `php artisan config:cache`.

## SSH / testing

- Alias: **`TrendsGCP`** — app at `/var/www/looptrends`, live at https://trends.roberttodds.com
- Production DB/uploads are **not** in git. Sync via SSH: mysqldump to `database/sync/production.sql`, `rsync` `public/uploads/` (see GCP-DEPLOY.md).
- Read production `.env` on server with `grep`; never commit secrets or run `migrate:fresh` on production.
